tar   -cvf  fileName  SourceFile          (Note:  -f  must come in last option,  -f  refer to  file name,     -cfv   X    Incorrect)

1-  Archive
    -c v f          fileName (wirh Red Color)

2- gzip
    -c z f          filename.gz

3- gzip2
    -cv j f         fileName.bz

4- xz
    -cv J f        fileName.xz



DeCompress
  - Replace "c" with "x" for Extraxt            , c => Compress  , x => Extract

    Ex.
       J            .xz
tar -xvjf backup.tar.biz2  --directory=/home
       z            .gzip
